This paper deals with the problem of serving requests in Software-Defined Networks (SDNs) with network function virtualization (NFV), which is a topic related to computer networks (cs.NI) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The paper also proposes an online algorithm for path computation and function placement, which involves optimization and algorithm design (cs.AL) and system and control theory (cs.SY). Finally, the paper deals with capacity constraints and maximizing benefits, which are topics related to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
